{{page-title (concat @model.game.name ' :: Charts')}}

<div class='general-content-box'>
  <h1>{{@model.game.name}} Â» Charts</h1>
</div>

<div class='general-content-box'>
  <h2>Charts and chart groups</h2>

  <p>These are defined in a hierarchy. Each chart has a chart type, and may have chart tag(s). If "Show charts together?" is activated for a chart group, that group can display rankings for each of its charts side by side.</p>

  <table class='data-table'>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Chart group / Chart</th>
        <th>Show charts together?</th>
        <th>Chart type</th>
        <th>Chart tags</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>

    <tbody>
      {{#each @model.chartHierarchy as |item|}}
        <ChartGroupDetails @item={{item}} @prefix='' />
      {{/each}}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<div class='general-content-box'>
  <h2>Chart tags</h2>

  <p>These are used for grouping charts together for purposes of defining total times/scores, and for defining ladder ranking formulas. The primary chart type determines how the chart tag's total is displayed and ordered (ascending or descending).</p>

  <table class='data-table'>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Name</th>
        <th>Total name</th>
        <th>Primary chart type</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>

    <tbody>
      {{#each @model.chartTags as |chartTag|}}
        <tr>
          <td>{{chartTag.name}}</td>
          <td>{{chartTag.totalName}}</td>
          <td>{{chartTag.primaryChartType.name}}</td>
        </tr>
      {{/each}}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>